Interaction & Diagnostic

Data upload

crime_df = 
  read_csv("cdi.csv") %>% 
  mutate(
    region = factor(region),
    pop_density = pop / area,
    beds_density = beds / area,
    docs_density = docs / area,
    crm_1000 = 1000 * crimes / pop
  ) %>% 
  dplyr::select(-crimes, -id, -area, -pop, -beds, -docs) %>% 
  dplyr::select(crm_1000, everything()) %>%
  drop_na()

EDA

crime_state = crime_df %>% 
  group_by(state) %>% 
  summarize(crime_rate = mean(crm_1000))

Fail to reject H0, so we keep the small model.

Thus, the fit model would be: model_selective = lm(crm_1000 ~ totalinc + poverty + hsgrad + beds_density + docs_density + region + pop_density, data = crime_df)

Potential Interaction

Candidate models

Thus the three candidate regression model should be:

model_1 = lm(crm_1000 ~ totalinc + poverty + hsgrad + beds_density + docs_density + region + pop_density + bagrad*poverty + + pcincome*region, data = crime_df)

model_2 = lm(crm_1000 ~ pop18 + hsgrad + bagrad + poverty + pcincome + 
    totalinc + region + pop_density + beds_density + bagrad*poverty + poverty*region, data = crime_df)

model_3 = lm(crm_1000 ~ pop18 + hsgrad + bagrad + poverty + pcincome + 
    totalinc + region + pop_density + beds_density + bagrad*poverty, data = crime_df)
